exchangedWTONtoTOS(address,uint256,uint2.details: exchange WTON to TOS using uniswap v3

exchangedWTONtoTOS2(address,uint256,uint.details: exchange WTON to TOS using uniswap v2

tokamakProcessedUnStaking(address,uint25.details: event on process unstaking in layer2 in tokamak

params.receiveTON: if is true ,TON , else is WTON

tokamakRequestedUnStaking(address,uint25.details: event on request unstaking the wtonAmount in layer2 in tokamak

tokamakRequestedUnStakingAll(address).details: event on request unstaking the amount of all in layer2 in tokamak

tokamakStaked(address,uint256).details: event on staking the staked TON in layer2 in tokamak

params.amount: the amount that stake to layer2

checkTokamak().details: If the tokamak addresses is not set, set the addresses.

exchangeWTONtoTOS(uint256,uint256,uint25.details: exchange holded WTON to TOS using uniswap

params._kind: the function type, if 0, use exactInputSingle function, else if, use exactInput function

returns.amountOut: the amount of exchanged out token

exchangeWTONtoTOSv2(uint256,uint256,uint.details: exchange holded WTON to TOS using uniswap-v2

params._kind: the function type, if 0, use exactInputSingle function, else if, use exactInput function

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

getUniswapInfo().details: get the addresses that used in uniswap interfaces

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

swapTONtoWTON(uint256,bool).details: Change the TON holded in contract have to WTON, or change WTON to TON.

params.toWTON: if it's true, TON->WTON , else WTON->TON

tokamakProcessUnStaking(address).details: process unstaking in layer2 in tokamak

tokamakRequestUnStaking(address,uint256).details: request unstaking the wtonAmount in layer2 in tokamak

tokamakRequestUnStakingAll(address).details: request unstaking the amount of all in layer2 in tokamak

tokamakStaking(address,uint256).details: staking the staked TON in layer2 in tokamak

params.stakeAmount: the amount that stake to layer2
